{
  "texts": [
    "Then for all O ′′ ⊆ O ′, O ′′ R ▷ σ ′.",
    "This establishes R-refinability +.The following lemma is the motivation for defining R ▷ as above.Informally, it says that ♢ ▷ can take us from the canonical encoding σ O of a regular open set O back to O itself.",
    "Although we have not yet defined all of F, the lemma holds no matter what further accessibility relations we define.",
    "Lemma 2.46.",
    "For any formula χ and model M based on the frame F, if χM = ↓σ O, then ♢ ▷ χ M = ↓O."
  ]
}